explanation: The solution uses a recursive backtracking approach to explore all possible valid string combinations by removing invalid parentheses. It maintains a set to store unique valid strings and prunes the search space based on the number of open and closed parentheses encountered.  The exponential time complexity arises from the branching factor of each recursive call, as it considers removing or keeping each parenthesis.

